channel.title: Server Not Online?
channel.description: Ok, this is kinda weird.. I portforwarded the server and everything.. and it works on MY computer... but for some reason it won't work on any other computer. I was thinking that the server was only connecting to Localhost which would explain why it only works on my computer.. idk its really confusing.. So, i decided to go to canyouseeme.org and check the port and see if its open.. And when it checks it comes back and says "Error: Couldn't find 43594 on "my ip" reason: Connection Refused." what does that mean.. i thought it means the firewall won't allow people to access the port on my server but. That doesn't explain why it works on my computer. Can someone help or do TeamViewer or anything.. Thanks.

item.title: Server Not Online?
item.dc:creator: @chains424 chains424
item.description:
@chains424 wrote:

1. Never use "Canyouseeme.org
it’s a piece of junk website that is never right. Honestly, it cannot detect rather your ports are open or not.
Google PFPortchecker and download it if you wish to see if your ports are open.

I just went to Canyouseeme.org and it said my ports weren’t open, but I know for a fact that they are.

You’re going to have to provide me more information so I can help better.

Did you go to your routers website and port forward from there?
